com.github.astefanich.broker.concurrent.threaded

Class ThreadedOrderQueue<T,E extends Order>

  • Object
    • ThreadedOrderQueue<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type: the dispatchable threshold type
    E - Elements: the type of order(s) to be contained within the queue
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    OrderQueue<T,E>, Runnable

    public class ThreadedOrderQueue<T,E extends Order>
extends Object
implements OrderQueue<T,E>, Runnable
    A simple OrderQueue implementation which stores orders in a TreeSet. Each queue runs in a separate thread.
    Author:
    AndrewStefanich

      • dequeue

        public E dequeue()
        Removes the highest dispatchable order in the queue. If there are orders, but they do not meet dispatch criteria, the order is not removed and null is returned.
        Specified by:

      • run

        public void run()
        Dispatches orders in a separate thread. This thread will wait if there are no dispatchable orders in the queue. Each dispatchable order is removed from the queue and passed to the callback. If there is no callback/orderprocessor registered, the order is simply revmoed from the queue.
        Specified by:
        run in interface Runnable
